Mulligatawny Soup

5 medium garlic cloves
2 large red onions
3-4 medium carrots, peeled
1 apple, peeled and cored
1 large yukon gold potato, peeled
1 fresh serrano pepper, stem removed
1" knob ginger
1" knob tumeric
2 c red lentil (masoor dhal) washed & rinsed
2x14oz cans full fat coconut milk
curry spices*
salt to taste

curry spices:
1 tsp each
 black peppercorns
 mustard seeds
 fennel seeds
 cumin seeds
 tumeric powder
 cinnamon sticks
 fresh curry leaves
 cardamom whole pods

Dice the garlic, onions, carrots, apple, potato, pepper, ginger, and tumeric into ~2cm cubes. Grind the peppercorns, mustard, fennel, and cumin seeds into powder in a spice grinder. Coat the bottom of a stockpot with a thin slick of vegetable oil and heat over medium high heat. Add fresh curry leaves, cardamom pods, and cinnamon sticks and cook for 1-2 min, stirring. Add all the remaining spices and the diced vegetables and stir again until the spices are evenly distributes among the vegetables. Cook for a few minutes, or until the vegetables begin to brown. Add lentils and stir, then add water just to cover everything in the pot. Cover and cook until vegetables and lentils are tender. Add coconut milk and bring back to a boil. Let the soup cool, blend, strain, and serve.
